One in three Turkish voters favor
Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan  as the next president, a
poll published by Aksam newspaper showed.  The poll by IKSara Research Company asked 2,055 people in
81 provinces of  Turkey  who they would support as the next
president and 36 percent said Erdogan, far ahead of other
possible candidates, the Istanbul-based newspaper reported.  The newspaper didnâ€™t give a margin of error for the survey
